-- Tottenham Hotspur in Talks to Sign Villa, Damiao: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   A l e x   D u f f
-- 2013-05-28T08:46:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-28/tottenham-hotspur-in-talks-to-sign-villa-damiao-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable Internet links.  Tottenham Talks  Tottenham is in talks to sign strikers David Villa and
Leandro Damiao from Barcelona and  Brazil ’s Internacional,
respectively, the  Daily Mail reported .  Villa would cost Spurs about 10 million pounds ($15.1
million) and Damiao 18 million pounds, according to the Mail.  Mourinho’s Assistant  Jose Mourinho is planning to bring Rui Faria with him to
Chelsea as his assistant coach, the  Sun reported .  Faria, 37, will also leave Real  Madrid  next week to follow
Mourinho back to  Stamford  Bridge, the newspaper added. They’ve
worked together since teaming up at  Portugal ’s Leiria in 2001
when Faria became fitness coach, the Sun said.  Arshavin Exit  Andrey Arshavin could return to Zenit St. Petersburg after
his Arsenal contract ended, the  Daily Mirror reported .  The Russian attacking midfielder, who turns 32 tomorrow,
has also had offers from Fenerbahce, Major League Soccer and the
Middle East, the Mirror said.  Hughes to Stoke  Mark Hughes is the leading contender to become Stoke City’s
manager, the  Daily Telegraph reported .  Hughes is expected to agree to a 12-month contract amid
opposition from Stoke fans, the Telegraph said.  Fulham Signing  Fulham is arranging to hire Marseille midfielder Morgan
Amalfitano on loan, the  Daily Mail reported .  The  France  international has struggled to settle at
Marseille since joining from Lorient in 2011, the Mail said.  To contact the reporters on this story:
